This article is a transcript of a press gaggle with Press Secretary Jay Carney. Carney discusses a range of topics including the Pentagon's announcement on women in combat, North Korea's provocative statements, the President's goal to work together with Congress, the nomination of Mary Jo White as chair of the Securities and Exchange Commission, the President's plan to replace the sequester, the confirmation of Richard Cordray, and the President's plans for immigration reform. Carney also mentions that the President will announce his intention to nominate Jack Lew as Treasury Secretary and that the President's decision on the Keystone Pipeline will be made by the State Department.